quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  43,46,"And indeed We already sent M?asu (Moses) with Our signs to Firaawn (Pharaoh) and his chiefs. So he said, \"Surely I am the Messenger of The Lord of the worlds"
  43,47,"Yet, as soon as he came to them with Our signs, only then did they laugh at them"
  43,48,"And in no way did We show them any sign except that it was greater than its sister sign; and We took (hold) of them with the torment, that possibly they would return"
  43,49,"And they said, \"O you sorcerer, invoke your Lord for us by what He has covenanted in your presence. Surely we (ourselves) will indeed be right-guided"
  43,50,"Yet, as soon as We lifted off them the torment, only then did they breach (their promise)"
  43,51,"And Firaawn (Pharaoh) called out upon his people (and) said, \"O my people, is not the kingdom of Misr (i.e., Egypt) mine, and are not these rivers running from beneath me? Do you not then behold"
  43,52,"Or even am I (not) more charitable (i.e., better) than this (fellow), who is contemptile and almost cannot make (his meaning) evident"
  43,53,"So, had armlets of gold been cast (i.e., bestoned on him) on him, or Angels had come with him in comradeship"
  43,54,"Then he induced levity (i.e., missed his people) on his people, so they obeyed him; surely they were an immoral people"
  43,55,"Then as soon as they provoked Our anger, (Or: behaved foolishly towards Us) We took vengeance on them; so We drowned them all together"
  43,56,So We made them a bygone (precedent) and a similitude to the later (generations)